{"questionId":"9069826","questionHtml":"<p>What is the standard enthalpy of formation, in kJ mol<sup>–1</sup>, of IF (g)?</p>\n<p>IF<sub>7</sub> (g) + I<sub>2</sub> (s) → IF<sub>5</sub> (g) + 2IF (g)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em>ΔH<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"^\\theta \">\n  <msup>\n    <mi></mi>\n    <mi>θ</mi>\n  </msup>\n</math></span></em>&nbsp;= –89 kJ</p>\n<p><em>ΔH</em><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"_f^\\theta \">\n  <msubsup>\n    <mi></mi>\n    <mi>f</mi>\n    <mi>θ</mi>\n  </msubsup>\n</math></span>&nbsp;(IF<sub>7</sub>) = –941 kJ mol<sup>–1</sup></p>\n<p><em>ΔH</em><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"_f^\\theta \">\n  <msubsup>\n    <mi></mi>\n    <mi>f</mi>\n    <mi>θ</mi>\n  </msubsup>\n</math></span>&nbsp;(IF<sub>5</sub>) = –840 kJ mol<sup>–1</sup></p>\n<p>A. –190</p>\n<p>B. –95</p>\n<p>C. +6</p>\n<p>D. +95</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>B</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9069826","referenceCode":"17N.1.hl.TZ0.16","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"What is the standard enthalpy of formation, in kJ mol–1, of IF (g)? IF7 (g) + I2 (s) → IF5 (g) + 2IF (g) ΔH θ = –89 kJ ΔH f θ (IF7) = –941 kJ mol–1 ΔH f θ (IF5) = –840 kJ mol–1 A. ","paper":"1","level":"hl","questionNumber":"16","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Additional higher level (AHL)","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 15: Energetics/thermochemistry","15.2 Entropy and spontaneity","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 15: Energetics/thermochemistry"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}